The paper deals with the design and analysis of a data structure, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The problem of maintaining a subset under insertion, deletion, and membership queries is a classic problem in data structures, and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the space complexity of the data structure, which is related to the field of data compression (cs.DM). The constant-time initialization and operation of the data structure involve the use of efficient algorithms and data structures, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of the data structure in space-efficient computing, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
